{"application": "software-mentions", "version": "0.8.0", "date": "2024-10-07T11:38+0000", "md5": "4CFB88C0FF847AACD22F3400A6FFE6F9", "mentions": [{"type": "software", "software-type": "software", "software-name": {"rawForm": "Kaldi", "normalizedForm": "Kaldi", "offsetStart": 0, "offsetEnd": 5}, "context": "Kaldi 1 is used to process all the steps of SV.", "mentionContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": true, "score": 0.9990488886833191}, "created": {"value": false, "score": 2.6464462280273438e-05}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 2.384185791015625e-07}}, "documentContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": true, "score": 0.9990488886833191}, "created": {"value": false, "score": 2.6464462280273438e-05}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 2.384185791015625e-07}}}, {"type": "software", "software-type": "software", "software-name": {"rawForm": "FaSnet", "normalizedForm": "FaSnet", "offsetStart": 0, "offsetEnd": 6}, "context": "FaSnet (filter-and-sum network) is a filter-based beamforming approach suitable for real-time low-latency applications [1].", "mentionContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": false, "score": 3.361701965332031e-05}, "created": {"value": false, "score": 0.0007849931716918945}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 2.384185791015625e-07}}, "documentContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": true, "score": 0.9999964237213135}, "created": {"value": false, "score": 0.14611685276031494}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 0.0007857084274291992}}}, {"type": "software", "software-type": "software", "software-name": {"rawForm": "FaSnet", "normalizedForm": "FaSnet", "offsetStart": 0, "offsetEnd": 6}, "context": "FaSnet degrades the SV performance as FaSnet introduces artifacts that distort the signal quality. ", "mentionContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": false, "score": 0.00020366907119750977}, "created": {"value": false, "score": 0.00016355514526367188}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 1.1920928955078125e-07}}, "documentContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": true, "score": 0.9999964237213135}, "created": {"value": false, "score": 0.14611685276031494}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 0.0007857084274291992}}}, {"type": "software", "software-type": "software", "software-name": {"rawForm": "FaSnet", "normalizedForm": "FaSnet", "offsetStart": 0, "offsetEnd": 6}, "context": "FaSnet incorporates a two-staged architecture.", "mentionContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": false, "score": 0.000574946403503418}, "created": {"value": false, "score": 0.00851529836654663}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 5.960464477539062e-07}}, "documentContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": true, "score": 0.9999964237213135}, "created": {"value": false, "score": 0.14611685276031494}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 0.0007857084274291992}}}, {"type": "software", "software-type": "software", "software-name": {"rawForm": "FaSnet", "normalizedForm": "FaSnet", "offsetStart": 8, "offsetEnd": 14}, "context": "We used FaSnet to obtain a first estimate of the speech signal s(T-F) and the noise signal n(T-F).", "mentionContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": true, "score": 0.9999964237213135}, "created": {"value": false, "score": 1.2040138244628906e-05}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 1.1920928955078125e-07}}, "documentContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": true, "score": 0.9999964237213135}, "created": {"value": false, "score": 0.14611685276031494}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 0.0007857084274291992}}}, {"type": "software", "software-type": "software", "software-name": {"rawForm": "FaSnet", "normalizedForm": "FaSnet", "offsetStart": 13, "offsetEnd": 19}, "context": "Furthermore, FaSnet Rank-1 MWF WPE achieves the best performance across the noise conditions, demonstrating our approach's efficacy even though the model was trained on synthetic data generated for generic, possibly mismatched, and spatial scenarios.", "mentionContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": false, "score": 0.0034342408180236816}, "created": {"value": false, "score": 0.0003336668014526367}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 1.1920928955078125e-07}}, "documentContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": true, "score": 0.9999964237213135}, "created": {"value": false, "score": 0.14611685276031494}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 0.0007857084274291992}}}, {"type": "software", "software-type": "software", "software-name": {"rawForm": "FaSnet", "normalizedForm": "FaSnet", "offsetStart": 29, "offsetEnd": 35}, "context": "We observed that integrating FaSnet with signal processing methods consistently improves against the baseline 1 https://github.com/kaldi-asr/kaldi ", "mentionContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": true, "score": 0.8759016990661621}, "created": {"value": false, "score": 8.58306884765625e-06}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 0.0007857084274291992}}, "documentContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": true, "score": 0.9999964237213135}, "created": {"value": false, "score": 0.14611685276031494}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 0.0007857084274291992}}}, {"type": "software", "software-type": "software", "software-name": {"rawForm": "FaSnet", "normalizedForm": "FaSnet", "offsetStart": 30, "offsetEnd": 36}, "context": "The training objective of the FaSnet model is to select a signal-level loss criterion based on the actual task needed to be solved.", "mentionContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": false, "score": 0.0015794038772583008}, "created": {"value": false, "score": 0.010275006294250488}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 1.1920928955078125e-07}}, "documentContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": true, "score": 0.9999964237213135}, "created": {"value": false, "score": 0.14611685276031494}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 0.0007857084274291992}}}, {"type": "software", "software-type": "software", "software-name": {"rawForm": "FaSnet", "normalizedForm": "FaSnet", "offsetStart": 34, "offsetEnd": 43}, "context": "The DNN-based approach implements FaSnet [1], a state-of-the-art neural beamforming technique for speech enhancement. ", "mentionContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": false, "score": 3.647804260253906e-05}, "created": {"value": false, "score": 0.14611685276031494}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 2.384185791015625e-07}}, "documentContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": true, "score": 0.9999964237213135}, "created": {"value": false, "score": 0.14611685276031494}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 0.0007857084274291992}}}, {"type": "software", "software-type": "software", "software-name": {"rawForm": "FaSnet", "normalizedForm": "FaSnet", "offsetStart": 38, "offsetEnd": 44}, "context": "FaSnet degrades the SV performance as FaSnet introduces artifacts that distort the signal quality. ", "mentionContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": false, "score": 0.00020366907119750977}, "created": {"value": false, "score": 0.00016355514526367188}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 1.1920928955078125e-07}}, "documentContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": true, "score": 0.9999964237213135}, "created": {"value": false, "score": 0.14611685276031494}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 0.0007857084274291992}}}, {"type": "software", "software-type": "software", "software-name": {"rawForm": "FaSnet", "normalizedForm": "FaSnet", "offsetStart": 41, "offsetEnd": 47}, "context": "The second approach is an integration of FaSnet with Rank 1 multi-channel Wiener filter [2] and a de-reverberation algorithm [3]. ", "mentionContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": false, "score": 9.620189666748047e-05}, "created": {"value": false, "score": 4.2557716369628906e-05}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 1.1920928955078125e-07}}, "documentContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": true, "score": 0.9999964237213135}, "created": {"value": false, "score": 0.14611685276031494}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 0.0007857084274291992}}}, {"type": "software", "software-type": "software", "software-name": {"rawForm": "Asteroid toolbox", "normalizedForm": "Asteroid toolbox", "offsetStart": 43, "offsetEnd": 64}, "context": "The FaSNet implementation is used from the Asteroid toolbox [25] and replaced the TCN blocks with DPRNN in contrast to the original FaSNet architecture, where TCN is used to predict the beamformed filters.", "mentionContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": true, "score": 0.6202976107597351}, "created": {"value": false, "score": 1.8715858459472656e-05}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 1.1920928955078125e-07}}, "documentContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": true, "score": 0.6202976107597351}, "created": {"value": false, "score": 1.8715858459472656e-05}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 1.1920928955078125e-07}}}, {"type": "software", "software-type": "software", "software-name": {"rawForm": "FaSnet", "normalizedForm": "FaSnet", "offsetStart": 47, "offsetEnd": 53}, "context": "We give noisy multichannel signals as input to FaSnet to separate noise and speech.", "mentionContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": true, "score": 0.9999381303787231}, "created": {"value": false, "score": 0.0020495057106018066}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 5.960464477539062e-07}}, "documentContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": true, "score": 0.9999964237213135}, "created": {"value": false, "score": 0.14611685276031494}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 0.0007857084274291992}}}, {"type": "software", "software-type": "software", "software-name": {"rawForm": "FaSnet", "normalizedForm": "FaSnet", "offsetStart": 67, "offsetEnd": 73}, "context": "The baseline BLSTM-based approaches perform poorly compared to the FaSnet-based approaches in all the noise conditions.", "mentionContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": false, "score": 0.00591123104095459}, "created": {"value": false, "score": 1.0609626770019531e-05}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 2.384185791015625e-07}}, "documentContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": true, "score": 0.9999964237213135}, "created": {"value": false, "score": 0.14611685276031494}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 0.0007857084274291992}}}, {"type": "software", "software-type": "software", "software-name": {"rawForm": "FaSnet", "normalizedForm": "FaSnet", "offsetStart": 104, "offsetEnd": 110}, "context": "Both stages use the temporal convolutional networks (TCN), enabling the lower latency processing of the FaSnet model.", "mentionContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": false, "score": 0.3136630654335022}, "created": {"value": false, "score": 4.458427429199219e-05}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 1.1920928955078125e-07}}, "documentContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": true, "score": 0.9999964237213135}, "created": {"value": false, "score": 0.14611685276031494}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 0.0007857084274291992}}}, {"type": "software", "software-type": "software", "software-name": {"rawForm": "pyroomacoustics toolbox", "normalizedForm": "pyroomacoustics toolbox", "offsetStart": 119, "offsetEnd": 145}, "context": "To simulate room effects, we have generated an RIR corpus of 10000 rooms for training and 3600 for evaluation with the pyroomacoustics toolbox [7]. ", "mentionContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": true, "score": 0.9957873225212097}, "created": {"value": false, "score": 0.0005429387092590332}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 1.1920928955078125e-07}}, "documentContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": true, "score": 0.9957873225212097}, "created": {"value": false, "score": 0.0005429387092590332}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 1.1920928955078125e-07}}}], "references": [], "runtime": 7759, "id": "d1adef61a9fc30ab2fe2bdd2a4609b3ada6ed621", "metadata": {"id": "d1adef61a9fc30ab2fe2bdd2a4609b3ada6ed621"}, "original_file_path": "../../datalake/Samuel/SOFTware-Sync/downloads/xml/hal-03619903.grobid.tei.xml", "file_name": "hal-03619903.grobid.tei.xml"}